A LITTLE HISTORY

Get to know a bit about what I have done in the past

  • 2006-2011

    Sgt in the United States Marine Corps

    In my five years, completed combat tours in Iraq and Afghanistan. These experiences continue to be incredibly influential in my personal and professional life. The Marine Corps allowed me to develop great leadership, communication and problem solving skills in high preassure situations.

  • 2012 - 2014

    Technology leads me to sales

    I knew that technology was a passion of mine and I wanted to work with it. My Account Mgmt position at IT Firm in Minneapolis allowed me to familiarize myself with a veriety of new platforms and services. I was able to increase professional services sales by 30% using the newest sales models and techniques

  • 2014-2015

    Take my management skills to the next level opening a Downtown Chicago restaurant

    My adventures in Chicago with Pinstripes were some of the most challenging I have had. The lgoistics alone of managing 80+ staff and 35,000 sq foot building alone proved challenging on a daily basis. Once the operation was up and running I know

  • December 2015

    THE BIG PIVOT

    I recenetly left my management role at downtown Chicago restaurant group and moved to Thailand to focus on pivoting my career towards web development. I have now spent 8 Months in Thailand focused on learning development languages like Javascript, HTML5, CSS3 and JQuery.

  • June 2016 - Present

    The Development Mindset

    I also spent an immense amount of time breaking building projects to gain a comfortability with the languages. The idea of thinking in the language and not just writing it was a big barrier to overcome. Most importantly I dedicated time to training my brain to think like a web developer. breaking down problems to their smallest sub problem and solving what I knew(10%) and Googling what I didn't(90%).
